what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
This command establishes an SSH connection to a remote server using the specified key file and creates a forwarded port from the local machine's port 5900 to the remote server's port 25900. The -C flag specifies that this is a command, not a interactive session, so no terminal will be opened.
